Date:  16/12/1897
Source:  Taranaki Herald
Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  A fisherman at Paraparaumu made a haul of twenty-five sharks on one line which had 450 hooks baited for schnapper. None were [sic] less than six feet, and one was a tiger shark nearly 18 feet long which bit a piece out of the boat and made a great fight before it was killed.
